Label: Groundwater Aquifer
Description: A body of saturated rock or sediment through which water can easily move (GWML2 standard).

Label: groundwater aquifer system
Description: Links a feature to the aquifer system it belongs to.

Label: groundwater aquifer system part
Description: Links an aquifer system to one of its component parts.

Label: Aquifer Water Feature
Description: A subsurface water feature representing an aquifer.

Label: Subsurface Water Feature
Description: A water feature below the earth's surface, such as aquifers and groundwater systems.

Label: Surface Water Feature
Description: A water feature at or above the earth's surface, such as rivers, lakes, and wetlands.

Label: Water Feature
Description: Any hydrologic feature containing or conveying water.

Label: Water Feature Representation
Description: A geometric or symbolic representation of a water feature.

Label: Flow Path Length
Description: The measured length of a flow path in the NHDPlus dataset.

Label: has COMID
Description: Links a feature to its Common Identifier (COMID) in the NHDPlus dataset.

Label: has feature code
Description: Links a feature to its feature code (FCODE) in the NHDPlus dataset.

Label: has feature type
Description: Links a feature to its feature type (FTYPE) in the NHDPlus dataset.

Label: has flow path length
Description: Links a flow path to its length measurement.

Label: has reach code
Description: Links a feature to its reach code in the NHDPlus dataset.

Label: source
Description: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.

Label: contributor
Description: An entity responsible for contributions to the resource.

Label: date created
Description: Date of creation of the resource.

Label: creator
Description: An entity responsible for making the resource.

Label: description
Description: An account of the resource.

Label: date modified
Description: Date on which the resource was changed.

Label: publisher
Description: An entity responsible for making the resource available.

Label: title
Description: A name given to the resource.

Label: connected to
Description: Indicates a topological connection or spatial contact.

Label: spatially related to
Description: A general topological connection or spatial contact.

Label: Quantity Kind
Description: The type or kind of quantity being measured (e.g., length, volume, flow rate).

Label: Quantity Value
Description: A measured or calculated value with an associated unit.

Label: Unit
Description: A unit of measurement (e.g., meter, liter, cubic foot per second).

Label: has quantity kind
Description: Links a quantity or unit to its quantity kind.

Label: has unit
Description: Links a quantity value to its unit of measurement.

Label: numeric value
Description: The numerical component of a quantity value.

Label: quantity value
Description: Links a quantity to its measured or calculated value.

Label: unit
Description: Specifies the unit of measurement.

Label: Illinois State Geological Survey Well
Description: A well documented by the Illinois State Geological Survey.

Label: Well Depth in Feet (IL)
Description: The depth of an Illinois well measured in feet.

Label: Well Purpose
Description: The intended purpose or use of a well.

Label: Well Yield
Description: The rate at which water can be withdrawn from a well.

Label: has ISWS ID
Description: Links a well to its Illinois State Water Survey identifier.

Label: has owner
Description: Links a well to its owner.

Label: well depth (IL)
Description: Links an Illinois well to its depth measurement.

Label: well purpose
Description: Links a well to its purpose classification.

Label: well yield
Description: Links a well to its yield measurement.

Label: Illinois SAW aquifer ID
Description: The SAWGraph identifier for an Illinois aquifer.

Label: Illinois SAW aquifer system ID
Description: The SAWGraph identifier for an Illinois aquifer system.

Label: Maine Geological Survey Well
Description: A well documented by the Maine Geological Survey.

Label: Well Depth in Feet
Description: The depth of a well measured in feet.

Label: Well Overburden Thickness in Feet
Description: The thickness of overburden (unconsolidated material) above bedrock at a well location, measured in feet.

Label: Well Type
Description: The type classification of a well (e.g., drilled, dug, driven).

Label: Well Use
Description: The purpose for which a well is used (e.g., domestic, irrigation, industrial).

Label: has use
Description: Links a well to its use classification.

Label: of well type
Description: Links a well to its type classification.

Label: well depth
Description: Links a well to its depth measurement.

Label: well overburden
Description: Links a well to its overburden thickness measurement.

Label: Maine MGS aquifer ID
Description: The Maine Geological Survey identifier for an aquifer.

Label: Maine SAW aquifer system ID
Description: The SAWGraph identifier for a Maine aquifer system.

Label: aquifer type
Description: The type classification of an aquifer (e.g., confined, unconfined, perched).

Label: Combined Distribution System
Description: A distribution system that combines water from multiple public water systems.

Label: PWS Service Area
Description: The geographic area served by a public water system.

Label: PWS Service Area Type
Description: The type classification of a public water system service area.

Label: PWS Source Water Type
Description: The type of water source used by a public water system (surface water, groundwater, etc.).

Label: PWS Sub-Feature
Description: A component of a public water system (e.g., well, intake, treatment plant).

Label: PWS Sub-Feature Activity
Description: The operational activity status of a public water system component.

Label: PWS Sub-Feature Type
Description: The type classification of a public water system component.

Label: Public Water System
Description: A system for providing water for human consumption that has at least 15 service connections or regularly serves 25+ people (EPA SDWIS).

Label: Community Water System
Description: A public water system that serves the same population year-round (e.g., municipalities).

Label: Groundwater-Based Public Water System
Description: A public water system that draws water from groundwater sources.

Label: Non-Community Water System
Description: A public water system that is not a community water system.

Label: Non-Transient Non-Community Water System
Description: A public water system that regularly serves at least 25 of the same people for 6+ months per year (e.g., schools, factories).

Label: Surface Water-Based Public Water System
Description: A public water system that draws water from surface water sources.

Label: Transient Non-Community Water System
Description: A public water system that serves the public but not the same people year-round (e.g., rest stops, campgrounds).

Label: buys from
Description: Indicates that one public water system purchases water from another.

Label: deactivation date
Description: The date when a public water system was deactivated.

Label: first report
Description: The date of the first report for a public water system.

Label: has activity
Description: Links a PWS sub-feature to its activity status.

Label: has method
Description: Specifies the method used by a PWS feature.

Label: has ownership
Description: Specifies the ownership type of a public water system.

Label: has part
Description: Links a public water system to one of its component parts.

Label: has permanent source
Description: Links a public water system to its permanent water source.

Label: has source
Description: Links a public water system to one of its water sources.

Label: in combined system
Description: Links a public water system to a combined distribution system it participates in.

Label: last report
Description: The date of the most recent report for a public water system.

Label: part of
Description: Links a component to the public water system it belongs to.

Label: population served
Description: The number of people served by the public water system.

Label: primary source type
Description: The primary type of water source used by the system.

Label: PWS name
Description: The name of the public water system.

Label: sells to
Description: Indicates that one public water system sells water to another.

Label: service area
Description: Links a public water system to its service area.

Label: service area type
Description: Specifies the type of service area.

Label: service connections
Description: The number of service connections provided by the public water system.

Label: source for
Description: Links a water source to the public water system it supplies.

Label: Administrative Region
Description: Administrative regions as defined by GADM.

Label: Administrative Region Level 0
Description: GADM level 0 administrative regions (countries).

Label: Administrative Region Level 1
Description: GADM level 1 administrative regions (states, provinces).

Label: Administrative Region Level 2
Description: GADM level 2 administrative regions (counties).

Label: Administrative Region Level 3
Description: GADM level 3 administrative regions (county subdivisions).

Label: Administrative Region Level 4
Description: GADM level 4 administrative regions.

Label: Administrative Region Level 5
Description: GADM level 5 administrative regions.

Label: Administrative Region Level 6
Description: GADM level 6 administrative regions.

Label: Cell
Description: A spatial cell.

Label: Region
Description: A spatial region.

Label: Road Segment
Description: A segment of a road network.

Label: S2 Cell
Description: A cell from the S2 discrete global grid system.

Label: S2 Cell Level 13
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 13.

Label: Statistical Area
Description: A geographic area for statistical data collection.

Label: ZIP Code Area
Description: A geographic area defined by a postal ZIP code.

Label: administrative part of
Description: Indicates administrative containment.

Label: spatially contains
Description: Indicates spatial containment.

Label: spatially crosses
Description: Indicates features cross each other.

Label: spatially equals
Description: Indicates spatial equality.

Label: spatially overlaps
Description: Indicates partial spatial overlap.

Label: spatially touches
Description: Indicates features touch at boundaries.

Label: spatially within
Description: Indicates spatial containment (inverse).

Label: spatial relation
Description: A spatial relationship between features.

Label: Feature
Description: A discrete spatial phenomenon in GeoSPARQL.

Label: Geometry
Description: A coherent set of direct positions in space in GeoSPARQL.

Label: Spatial Object
Description: Anything spatial in GeoSPARQL.

Label: as WKT
Description: The WKT serialization of a geometry.

Label: default geometry
Description: The default geometric representation of a feature.

Label: has default geometry
Description: Links a feature to its default geometric representation.

Label: has geometry
Description: Links a feature to its geometric representation.

Label: Multi-Polygon
Description: A collection of polygons (Simple Features).

Label: Polygon
Description: A two-dimensional geometric primitive (Simple Features).

Label: domain includes
Description: Relates a property to a class that constitutes one of its expected types for the subject.

Label: name
Description: The name of the item.

Label: range includes
Description: Relates a property to a class that constitutes one of its expected types for the value.

Label: Canal
Description: An artificial waterway constructed to allow the passage of boats or ships, or for irrigation.

Label: Catchment
Description: A physiographic unit with defined extent draining to a common outlet.

Label: Catchment Realization
Description: A geometric representation of a catchment boundary.

Label: Elementary Flow Path
Description: An indivisible flow path segment in a hydrologic network.

Label: Estuary
Description: The tidal mouth of a large river where the tide meets the stream.

Label: Flow Path
Description: A linear hydrologic feature representing the path of water flow.

Label: Hydrologic Feature
Description: The abstract supertype of all hydrologic features in the HY Features ontology.

Label: Impoundment
Description: A body of water confined by a dam, dike, floodgate, or other barrier.

Label: Lagoon
Description: A shallow body of water separated from a larger body of water by barrier islands or reefs.

Label: Lake
Description: A natural or artificial body of standing water.

Label: Main Stem
Description: The principal course of a river or stream.

Label: River
Description: A large natural stream of water flowing in a channel to the sea, a lake, or another river.

Label: Water Body
Description: A body of water such as a lake, reservoir, river, or estuary.

Label: downstream flow path
Description: Links a flow path to another flow path that is immediately downstream.

Label: downstream flow path (transitive closure)
Description: Links a flow path to all flow paths that are downstream (transitive property).

Label: encompassing catchment
Description: Links a feature to the catchment that contains it.

Label: realized catchment
Description: Links a catchment realization to the catchment it represents.

Label: upstream flow path
Description: Links a flow path to another flow path that is immediately upstream.

Label: upstream water body
Description: Links a feature to a water body that is upstream.
